                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> postParams,
                 @Nullable
                 AccessTokenRetriever retriever)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Creates a new LevelUpV13Request from a URL. This request will attempt to append the user's access_token to the request if the AccessTokenRetriever passed is not null and returns a non-null AccessToken.
        Parameters:
        context - the Application context.
        method - the HttpMethod for this request.
        url - the request URL. This can include query parameters.
        postParams - the body of the request if its a post.
        retriever - implementation of AccessTokenRetriever to use to try to append the access token to this request.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the URI specified isn't an absolute URL.
